# Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

## Server Configuration
```env
PORT=4000
```

## Security
```env
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-here
APP_SCHEME=iscitakip
```

## Email (SMTP)
```env
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
SMTP_FROM=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_SECURE=1
```

## Branding
```env
BRAND_NAME=Bavaxe
```

## OneSignal Push Notifications
```env
ONESIGNAL_APP_ID=your-onesignal-app-id
ONESIGNAL_REST_API_KEY=your-onesignal-rest-api-key
```

## Payment (Shopier)
```env
SHOPIER_PLUS_PRODUCT_LINK=https://shopier.com/your-store/product-id
SHOPIER_BUSINESS_PRODUCT_LINK=https://shopier.com/your-store/product-id
SHOPIER_PLUS_PRODUCT_ID=product-id
SHOPIER_BUSINESS_PRODUCT_ID=product-id
```

## Google OAuth
```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
```

## API Configuration
```env
# Production backend URL (Render)
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://isci-takip-app.onrender.com
```

## Important Notes

> [!WARNING]
> **DO NOT** add `NODE_ENV=production` to this file. It will prevent Expo from loading environment variables correctly.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `EXPO_PUBLIC_` prefix is required for variables that need to be accessible in the Expo app.

> [!TIP]
> For local development, you can override the API URL:
> ```env
> EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
> ```
